{"title": "New global reality, not alignments, behind Malaysia\u2019s pursuit of Brics membership", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2024-08-02", "content": "KUALA LUMPUR \u2013 Malaysia\u2019s declared desire to join the Brics grouping \u2013 most recently espoused during a visit by Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov to Kuala Lumpur on July 28 \u2013 is deepening concerns over whether Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim is leaning away from Western powers.\nIn his 20 months in power, Datuk Seri Anwar has staunchly condemned the United States and other allies of Israel over the prolonged conflict in Gaza, and repeatedly defended Beijing against \u201cChina-phobia\u201d."}